    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer925246413" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11640446825755303142">More nostalgia. Yes, this is definitely a middle book. Yes, it has weird time-jumps and omissions (many of which, I&apos;m sure, have subsequently been filled in with the Lost Chronicles; but I haven&apos;t read those yet). Yes, the writing for the most part remains adequate at best. And yes, the events at the climax of the book <a class='jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction'>(view spoiler)</a><span class='spoilerContainer' style='display: none'>[with Sturm at the Tower of the High Clerist <a class='jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction'>(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> still hit me surprisingly hard.<br/><br/>So yeah, somewhere between .5 and 1 of the stars are for nostalgia (and I</span>
  <span id="freeText11640446825755303142" style="display:none">More nostalgia. Yes, this is definitely a middle book. Yes, it has weird time-jumps and omissions (many of which, I'm sure, have subsequently been filled in with the Lost Chronicles; but I haven't read those yet). Yes, the writing for the most part remains adequate at best. And yes, the events at the climax of the book <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[with Sturm at the Tower of the High Clerist <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> still hit me surprisingly hard.<br /><br />So yeah, somewhere between .5 and 1 of the stars are for nostalgia (and I <i>still</i> wish GoodReads would give us half-stars), but I'm comfortable with a 4 star rating.</span>
